Identifies the API resource's type. The value will be youtube#video
The Etag of this resource
The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the video
The date and time that the video was published.
The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the channel that the video was uploaded to.
The video's title
The video's description
The YouTube video category associated with the video
The language of the text in the video resource's snippet.title and snippet.description properties
The localized video title
The localized video description
Specifies the language spoken in the video's default audio track
The status of the uploaded video.Valid values := (deleted, failed, processed, rejected, uploaded)

This value explains why a video failed to upload. This property is only present if the uploadStatus property indicates that the upload failed. valid values :=(codec, conversion, emptyFile, invalidFile, tooSmallupload, Aborted)

This value explains why YouTube rejected an uploaded video. This property is only present if the uploadStatus property indicates that the upload was rejected. Valid values:=(claim, copyright, duplicate, inappropriate, legal, length, termsOfUse, trademark, uploaderAccountClosed, uploaderAccountSuspended)
The video's privacy status.Valid values := (private, public, unlisted)
The date and time when the video is scheduled to publish. It can be set only if the privacy status of the video is private
The video's license
This value indicates whether the video can be embedded on another website
This value indicates whether the extended video statistics on the video's watch page are publicly viewable. By default, those statistics are viewable
The number of times the video has been viewed
The number of users who have indicated that they liked the video
The number of users who have indicated that they disliked the video
This property has been deprecated. The deprecation is effective as of August 28, 2015. The property's value is now always set to 0
The number of comments for the video

Important: This property has been deprecated as of November 10, 2016. The API no longer returns values for this property, and any topics associated with a video are now returned by the topicDetails.relevantTopicIds[] property value.
The length of the uploaded video in milliseconds
The uploaded video file's combined (video and audio) bitrate in bits per second
The date and time when the uploaded video file was created.
The localized by the (key) video title
The localized by the (key) video description.
Identifies the API resource's type. The value will be youtube#commentThread
The Etag of this resource
The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the comment thread
The YouTube channel that is associated with the comments in the thread
If the comments are about a video then the value identifies The ID of the video that the comments refer to. if the comments refer to the channel itself this property will not have a value
The thread's top-level comment. The property's value is a comment
This setting indicates whether the current viewer can reply to the thread
The total number of replies that have been submitted in response to the top-level comment
This setting indicates whether the thread, including all of its comments and comment replies, is visible to all YouTube users.
A list of one or more replies to the top-level comment
Identifies the API resource's type. The value will be youtube#comment
The Etag of this resource
The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the comment
The display name of the user who posted the comment
The URL for the avatar of the user who posted the comment
The URL of the comment author's YouTube channel, if available
The ID of the comment author's YouTube channel, if available
The YouTube channel that is associated with the comments in the thread
If the comments are about a video then the value identifies The ID of the video that the comments refer to. if the comments refer to the channel itself this property will not have a value
The comment's text. The text can be retrieved in either plain text or HTML

The original, raw text of the comment as it was initially posted or last updated. The original text is only returned if it is accessible to the authenticated user, which is only guaranteed if the user is the comment's author.
The unique ID of the parent comment. This property is only set if the comment was submitted as a reply to another comment
This setting indicates whether the current viewer can rate the comment

The rating the viewer has given to this comment. Note that this property does not currently identify dislike ratings, though this behavior is subject to change. In the meantime the values are :=(like, none)
The total number of likes
The comment's moderation status values := (heldForReview, likelySpam, published, rejected)
The date and time when the comment was orignally published
The date and time when the comment was last updated
Identifies the API resource's type. The value will be youtube#channel
The Etag of this resource
The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the channel
The channel's title
The channel's description
The channel's custom URL
The date and time that the channel was created
The language of the text in the channel resource's snippet.title and snippet.description properties
The localized channel title
The localized channel description
The country with which the channel is associated
The ID of the playlist that contains the channel's liked videos
The ID of the playlist that contains the channel's favorite videos
The ID of the playlist that contains the channel's uploaded videos
This property has been deprecated. The property's value is always set to HL. The API now returns an empty list in response to requests for playlist details
This property has been deprecated. The property's value is always set to WL. The API now returns an empty list in response to requests for playlist
The number of times the channel has been viewed
The number of comments for the channel
The number of subscribers that the channel has
Indicates whether the channel's subscriber count is publicly visible
The number of videos uploaded to the channel
A list of topic IDs associated with the channel. This property has been deprecated as of November 10, 2016.
A list of Wikipedia URLs that describe the channel's content
Privacy status of the channel. values := (private, public, unlisted)
Indicates whether the channel data identifies a user that is already linked to either a YouTube username or a Google+ account.

Indicates whether the channel is eligible to upload videos that are more than 15 minutes long. This property is only returned if the channel owner authorized the API request, values := (allowed, disallowed, eligible)
The channel's title. The title has a maximum length of 30 characters
The channel description, which appears in the channel information box on your channel page
Keywords associated with your channel. The value is a space-separated list of strings
This setting determines whether user-submitted comments left on the channel page need to be approved by the channel owner to be publicly visible. The default value is false.
This setting indicates whether YouTube should show an algorithmically generated list of related channels on your channel page

This setting indicates whether the channel page should display content in a browse or feed view. For example, the browse view might display separate sections for uploaded videos, playlists, and liked videos. The feed view, on the other hand, displays the channel's activity feed.
The title that displays above the featured channels module.
The video that should play in the featured video module in the channel page's browse view for unsubscribed viewers.
A prominent color that complements the channel's content
The language of the text in the channel resource's snippet.title and snippet.description properties.
The country with which the channel is associated
The ID of the content owner linked to the channel
The date and time of when the channel was linked to the content owner
The localized by the (key) channel title
The localized by the (key) channel description.
